{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"round cake tin (Ø 26-28 cm), skewer, oven","id":"r178838","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-C1OEYkN0Izs\/XZWp_ek2MzI\/AAAAAAAAfRk\/ku09Cx3j310sETpReMHkEDWxGDlcr0p0wCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_9UqMVu_Jl9Bo7q1B.png","title":"Apple cake","publishedAt":"2018-04-10T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"content":"3 - 4 apples, tart (approx. 180 g each)"},{"content":"130 g butter, unsalted, softened, cut into pieces, plus extra for greasing"},{"content":"3 eggs"},{"content":"150 g sugar"},{"content":"30 g brandy              (optional)"},{"content":"200 g plain flour"},{"content":"1 Tbsp baking powder (15 g)"},{"content":"1 pinch salt"},{"content":"icing sugar, for dusting"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"5 g","fat":"16 g","uom":"per 1 slice","carbohydrates":"46 g","calories":"1492 kJ \/ 356 kcal"},"preparations":[{"content":"Preheat oven to 180°C. Grease a round cake tin (Ø 26-28 cm) and set aside."},{"content":"Peel apples, cut in quarters and remove core and seeds. With a sharp knife, make parallel incisions on the outside of the apple, cutting down but taking care not to cut completely through. Set apple quarters aside."},{"content":"Place butter, eggs, sugar, brandy (if using), flour, baking powder and salt in mixing bowl and mix <b>20 sec\/speed 6<b>. Pour mixture into cake tin and spread evenly with spatula. Place reserved apple quarters on top, one next to the other, with incisions facing up."},{"content":"Bake for 30-40 minutes (180°C) until a skewer inserted in centre of cake comes out clean. Allow cake to cool in tin for approx. 10 minutes before transferring to a serving plate. Dust top of cake with icing sugar before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["You can leave the apples unpeeled.","If a smaller Ø tin is used, increase baking time (e.g. <b>40-45 minutes<b> for a <b>Ø 24 cm tin).<b> Fewer apples will be necessary for topping the smaller surface of the cake.","Apples can be replaced with pears (prepared as directed for the apples), plums (halved, stones removed), peaches (halved, stones removed) and prepared as directed for the apples), apricots (halved, stones removed), or any other fruit to your taste. The amount of fruit pieces depends on the size of the cake. You need enough to distribute evenly over the surface of the cake.","Brandy can be replaced with rum."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h","8 slices"]}